@ksindi -- `PlaidServerErrors` are generally ephemeral errors on the Plaid server and may often be resolved by retrying the request. 

If you're seeing this error consistently when calling `plaid_client.exchange_token(public_token)`, can you please open a case via the [Plaid Dashboard](https://dashboard.plaid.com/support) so that we can investigate?

The [Plaid Help Center](https://support.plaid.com/customer/en/portal/topics/973215-error-code-resolution) section on error codes is also a great resource about how to handle various classes of errors.

